{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://digbmc.github.io/pta-manifests/phan/phan-10441/manifest.json","type":"Manifest","label":{"none":["PHAN-10441"]},"metadata":[{"label":{"none":["Timestamp"]},"value":{"none":["1:04:41"]}},{"label":{"none":["Film"]},"value":{"none":["Phantom Thread"]}},{"label":{"none":["Distance"]},"value":{"none":["close-up"]}},{"label":{"none":["Angle"]},"value":{"none":["low"]}},{"label":{"none":["Location"]},"value":{"none":["interior"]}},{"label":{"none":["Movement"]},"value":{"none":["fixed"]}},{"label":{"none":["Composition"]},"value":{"none":["two shot"]}}],"summary":{"none":["A woman looks up fondly at a man."]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-10441/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"homepage":[{"id":"PHAN-10441","type":"Text","format":"text/html","label":{"none":["Object homepage"]}}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-10441/canvas/1","type":"Canvas","height":1080,"width":1920,"label":{"none":["PHAN-10441"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-10441/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-10441/canvas/1/annopage-1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-10441/canvas/1/annopage-1/anno-1","type":"Annotation","motivation":"painting","target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-10441/canvas/1","body":{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-10441/tiles/full/1920,1080/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":1080,"width":1920,"service":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-10441/tiles","type":"ImageService3","profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-10441/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-10441/canvas/1/bb6e5a33-4be3-4b18-9f3a-da7873693fac","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-30T18:25:07.527Z","creator":"Tallulah Stallvik","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>Ethan Warren aptly points out a parallel between <em>Phantom Thread</em> and <em>Boogie Nights</em> and their engagement with the theme of auteurism: “If both <em>Boogie Nights </em>and <em>Phantom Thread </em>deal with artists either unable or unwilling to create a work/life balance, the latter might be seen as a self-aware revision of the former. After <em>Phantom Thread</em>’s release, Anderson expressed chagrin at the single-minded focus he lavished on his own work at the expense of relationships early in his career, and it is thus fitting that Jack’s quixotic devotion to his dream of creating a narratively worthy skin flick is never significantly questioned; <em>Phantom Thread</em>, on the other hand, is a feature-length inquisition into monomaniacal auteurism, and the double meaning of ‘House’ within the world of high fashion—representing both ‘home’ and ‘commercial operation’—serves as the ideal refinement of the upstairs/downstairs Horner domicile” (Warren, <em>The Cinema of Paul Thomas Anderson</em>, 40).&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-10441/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:34.49032988726444,27.704487346635673,315.7898509174312,261.231364678899"}}}]}]}]}